OL,3,EMARIO KART 64GNintendo 64 ````Ux}=  x~|
OL,4,                               U'a|wk
OL,5,B"So, firstly Nintendo managed U`///{5n'
OL,6,Bto make the multi-player mode U*~}|>
OL,7,Bawful by having battle arenas U8<;6
OL,8,Bin which you couldn't see the Um}e/!'
OL,9,Bother drivers, and then secondly they  
OL,10,Bmessed it up by having bland courses.  
OL,12,F"Where was the trackside detail? It was
OL,13,Fall flat washes of colour and          
OL,14,Funpleasantly smooth hills. Gamers are  
OL,15,Fused to aeroplanes taking off and      
OL,16,Fspinning windmills in their racers.    
OL,17,FWhat did you get in Mario Kart 64?     
OL,18,FNothing - the courses looked as if they
OL,19,Fwere made out of blancmange and that." 
